Contacting Customers

Responding to Inquiries

1. When contacting customers to respond to inquiries, I will ensure that I am prepared and have all necessary information readily available. This includes having access to the customer's file, understanding their concerns, and being able to provide clear and concise answers to their questions. 2. I will listen attentively to the customer's inquiry, ask clarifying questions if necessary, and provide a detailed response that addresses their concerns.

Notifying Customers of Claim Investigation Results

1. When notifying customers of claim investigation results, I will ensure that I am empathetic and understanding of their situation. I will clearly explain the outcome of the investigation, including any decisions made regarding their claim. 2. I will also provide additional information or resources as needed, such as information on next steps or appeal processes.

Notifying Customers of Planned Adjustments

1. When notifying customers of planned adjustments, I will ensure that I am transparent and clear in my communication. I will explain the reason for the adjustment, the impact it will have on their account, and any next steps they need to take. 2. I will also be available to answer any questions or concerns the customer may have, and provide additional information or resources as needed.
